content: Logo for the editors header - embedded mode

comment.text: The translation key "LogoDocsEditorEmbedded" is used to display the logo name and size for the embedded editor header in a specific UI component. It appears on a settings page and displays metadata about a logo, including its name and dimensions, when the user views an editor icon.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'شعار ترويسة المحررين - الوضع المضمن' doesn't fully convey the meaning of "Logo for the editors header - embedded mode".  'ترويسة' (header) is correct, but 'الوضع المضمن' (embedded mode) is a more literal translation and might not be the most natural phrasing in Arabic. A more user-friendly equivalent would be something along the lines of 'شعار رأسية المحررين - الطريقة المدمجة' or 'شعار رأسية التحرير - الوضع المدمج'.

The translation doesn't fully capture the meaning of 'embedded mode'. 'Quraşdırılmış rejim' is technically correct but lacks the nuance of 'embedded'. A more accurate translation would convey the sense of being integrated or contained within something.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Redaktor başlığı - daxili rejim üçün loqo

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'Logo editorin ylätunnisteeseen - upotettu tila' doesn't fully convey the meaning of 'Logo for the editors header - embedded mode'. The phrase 'ylätunnisteeseen' (to the header) is a bit clunky and 'upotettu tila' (embedded mode) is literal and might not be the most natural way to express 'embedded' in this context. A more natural rendering would be something along the lines of 'Logo editorin otsikkoon - sisällytetty tila' or 'Logo editorin otsikossa - upotettuna'.

The translation 'Խմբագիրների վերնագրի պատկերանշան՝ ներկառուցված ռեժիմ' is a literal translation but doesn't quite capture the nuance of 'Logo for the editors header - embedded mode'. A more natural phrasing might be 'Խմբագիրների վերնագրի պատկերանշան՝ ներկառուցված աշխատանքային ռեժիմ' or 'Խմբագրի վերնագրի պատկերանշան՝ ներկառուցված ռեժիմ'.

The word 'ຝັງ' (fang) is a valid term for embedded, but 'ຝັງ' (fang) is generally used in a more literal sense (e.g., burying something). A more nuanced translation might be better depending on the context.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider 'ລັກສະນະຝັງ' (laksana fang) which implies 'embedded feature' or 'embedded mode' for greater clarity.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'Logotips redaktoru galvenei - iegultais režīms' is a bit literal and doesn't flow naturally in Latvian. 'Logotips' is correct, but 'redaktoru galvenei' is awkward. 'Galvenei' refers to the header, but it's phrased oddly.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Logotips redaktoru galvenes virsrakstā - iegultais režīms

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The two parts of the translation are joined by a hyphen, which might be too abrupt. A colon or a more descriptive phrase might improve readability.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Logotips redaktoru galvenes virsrakstā: iegultais režīms

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The term "koptekst" isn't the most natural translation for "header." "Header" often refers to the top bar of an interface. A more natural Dutch translation might be 'koof' or 'bovenbalk'.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Logo voor de koof van de editors - ingesloten modus

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation "සංස්කරකවල ශ්‍රීර්ෂයට ලාංඡනය - කාවැද්දූ ප්‍රකාරය" does not accurately convey the meaning of "Logo for the editors header - embedded mode".  "කාවැද්දූ ප්‍රකාරය" (literally 'stuck/embedded manner') is not the most natural way to describe 'embedded mode'. A better translation for 'embedded mode' would be something like 'ඇතුළත ක්‍රියාකාරිත්වය' or 'බද්ධ ප්‍රකාරය'. The word 'header' is not explicitly mentioned, so it's unclear if 'ශ්‍රීර්ෂයට' is required.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider alternatives like:  'සංස්කරකවල ශ්‍රීර්ෂයට ලාංඡනය - බද්ධ ප්‍රකාරය' or 'සංස්කරකවල ශ්‍රීර්ෂයට ලාංඡනය - ඇතුළත ක්‍රියාකාරිත්වය'.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The term 'embedded mode' is not accurately translated. 'Vdelan način' literally translates to 'embedded way' which is not the intended meaning of 'embedded mode'. A more accurate translation would convey the sense of being integrated or built-in.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Logotip za glavo urednikov - integriran način

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'Логотип за заглавље уређивача - уграђени режим' is a literal translation but could be more natural in Serbian. 'Заглавље' can sound a bit formal in this context.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Лого за мени уређивача - уграђени режим

ai_spell_check_issues.description: While not strictly incorrect, using 'лого' instead of 'логотип' is more common and concise in Serbian for 'logo'.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Лого за мени уређивача - уграђени режим

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The term 'režim' is not the best translation for 'mode' in this context. It implies a more complex system or state. A better translation would be 'način'.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Logotip za zaglavlje uređivača - ugrađeni način

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation "Editör başlığı logosu – gömülü mod" is a literal translation but sounds awkward in Turkish. A more natural phrasing would be "Editör başlığı için logo - yerleşik mod". "Gömülü mod" can feel too technical for a user-facing setting.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Editör başlığı için logo - yerleşik mod

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The hyphen usage is acceptable but could potentially be improved depending on the broader style guide. A space might improve readability.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Editör başlığı için logo - yerleşik mod

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'Logo cho tiêu đề của biên tập viên - chế độ nhúng' is somewhat literal and doesn't flow naturally in Vietnamese. 'Biên tập viên' is correct for 'editor', but the phrasing around the header is clunky.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Logo tiêu đề dành cho biên tập viên - chế độ nhúng

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The use of a hyphen to connect phrases can feel awkward in Vietnamese. While not strictly incorrect, it impacts readability.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider removing the hyphen and rephrasing for smoother flow.  For example, 'Logo tiêu đề dành cho biên tập viên - chế độ nhúng' or 'Logo cho tiêu đề biên tập viên - chế độ nhúng'.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation '编辑器标头徽标 - 嵌入模式' doesn't fully capture the nuance of 'Logo for the editors header - embedded mode'. While '编辑器标头' correctly translates 'editors header', '徽标' (hui biao) means 'logo' but it's a slightly formal and less common term.  A more natural and commonly used term would be '图标' (tu ao) which translates to 'icon'. The overall flow feels slightly stiff.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: 编辑器标头图标 - 嵌入模式
